comments: Theis (HOU) firms up in a screening position in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs to his side as he goes over the pick.
Theis (HOU) establishes himself in a screening position in Dort's (OKC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact on the pick.
Dort (OKC) establishes himself in front of Gordon (HOU) and absorbs the contact on the drive that dislodges him from his defensive position.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) cleanly deflects the pass away from Theis (HOU) and Bazley (OKC) secures the loose ball.
Mathews (HOU) reaches for the ball and avoids making any contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm on his steal attempt in transition.
Theis (HOU) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Theis (HOU) jumps toward and delivers contact by turning his body into Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC), which affects his driving shot attempt.
Theis (HOU) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm, which does not affect his SQBR at the start of his transition play.

During the transition play, Gordon (HOU) establishes himself in a legal guarding position in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and any contact to his side as Gilgeous-Alexander goes around him is marginal.

Mathews (HOU) makes contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt. Replay review of the foul called on Mathews (HOU) determined that the foul did not meet the criteria for a flagrant foul and remained a common foul.
Dort (OKC) is established in Gordon's (HOU) path and avoids making any contact with Gordon's arm when he temporarily loses control of his dribble as he changes directions.
Theis (HOU) drops the ball and legally regathers it to pass.
Dort (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Gordon (HOU).
From all available angles it appears Brooks (HOU) makes clean ball contact to dislodge it from Mann (OKC) on his driving shot attempt.
There is no clear and conclusive camera angle to overturn the call on the court of the ball being touched last by Brooks (HOU) before going out of bounds.
Gordon (HOU) places a resting forearm to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) front during the drive, and the contact is marginal as it does not affect his SQBR.
Bazley (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Tate (HOU).
Bazley (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Tate's (HOU) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
At the end of the drive, Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) stops his forward momentum and releases from the contact with Theis (HOU) for his step back jump shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) commits a take foul on Theis (HOU).
Tate (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position on Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) at the end of the drive and Gilgeous-Alexander dribbles the ball off of his own heel.
Theis (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position as he moves alongside of Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during the driving shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) commits a take foul on Mathews (HOU).
Jerome (OKC) does not release the throw-in within five seconds.
During the screen on the inbounds, Tate (HOU) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Dort (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in Tate's (HOU) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Tate (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position next to Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during his jump shot attempt.
